com.emc.atmos.api

Class ObjectPath

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.emc.atmos.api.ObjectPath
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ObjectIdentifier

    public class ObjectPath
extends java.lang.Object
implements ObjectIdentifier
    Represents the full path to an object within a subtenant namespace. Paths always start with a slash. Directories always end with a slash and non-directories never end with a slash.

        public ObjectPath(java.lang.String path)

      • ObjectPath

        public ObjectPath(ObjectPath parent,
          java.lang.String path)
        Constructs a new path underneath a parent directory.
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent directory under which this new path exists (must end with a slash).
        path - The relative path to this object under the parent directory (may begin with a slash, but it will be ignored).

      • ObjectPath

        public ObjectPath(ObjectPath parent,
          DirectoryEntry directoryEntry)
        Constructs a new path from a parent directory and (what is assumed to be) one of its directory entries. The resulting path will be a directory or file consistent with the directoryEntry.
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent directory under which this new path exists (must end with a slash).
        directoryEntry - A directory entry of an object (presumed to be under the parent path)
